## LINQ & Collections

### Prefer LINQ Method Syntax
```csharp
// GOOD - Method syntax
var activeUsers = users
    .Where(u => u.IsActive)
    .OrderBy(u => u.CreatedAt)
    .Select(u => new UserDto { Email = u.Email })
    .ToList();

// ACCEPTABLE - Query syntax for complex joins
var result = from user in users
             join role in roles on user.Id equals role.UserId
             where user.IsActive
             select new { user, role };
```

### Avoid Multiple Enumeration
```csharp
// BAD - Multiple enumeration
var users = GetUsers();
if (users.Any()) { }
var count = users.Count();  // Enumerates again

// GOOD - Materialize once
var users = GetUsers().ToList();
if (users.Any()) { }
var count = users.Count;  // No re-enumeration
```

