## Null Handling

### Nullable Reference Types (Enabled)
```csharp
#nullable enable

public class User
{
    public string Email { get; set; } = string.Empty;  // Non-nullable, must initialize
    public string? MiddleName { get; set; }  // Nullable, can be null
}
```

### Null-Coalescing & Pattern Matching
```csharp
// Null-coalescing
var name = user.MiddleName ?? "N/A";
var result = GetUser() ?? throw new InvalidOperationException("User not found");

// Pattern matching
if (user is null)
    return NotFound();

if (user is not null && user.IsActive)
    return Ok(user);

// Null-conditional operator
var email = user?.Email?.ToLower();
```

